Business Brief -- Coles Myer Ltd.:
   Concern to Advance Plan
   To Sell 60% of Subsidiary
It said it will offer 100 million ordinary or common
shares in Progressive Enterprises at an issue price of 2 New
Zealand dollars (US$1.09) a share. Progressive Enterprises,
which is wholly owned, was acquired by Coles Myer in 1988.
Assets included in the sale are a supermarket chain and
restaurant network.
   The company said that the reoffering of stock to New
Zealand investors makes the refloat of Progressive
Enterprises one of the largest offerings in New Zealand in
recent years.
   Coles Myer said it intends to retain a "significant equity
holding of at least about 30%" and intends to remain a major
Progressive Enterprises shareholder for the foreseeable
future.